events.description: The S&P Global Singapore PMI climbed to 56.8 in January 2026, signaling the fastest expansion since October.

facts.fact_text: The S&P Global Singapore PMI rose to 56.8 in January 2026 from 54.1 in December.

evidences.evidence_text: The S&P Global Singapore PMI climbed to 56.8 in January 2026 from December’s four-month low of 54.1.

facts.fact_text: Singapore's private sector activity has grown for 12 consecutive months.

evidences.evidence_text: The latest reading signaled the 12th consecutive month of growth in private sector activity

claims.claim_text: The expansion in private sector activity was driven by a sharp increase in new orders.
